Your two Play Store questions
"Users should only need to update the app, not get a new app" — this is just normal app versioning, and it's automatic as long as you keep publishing under the same package name / bundle ID and just bump the version number each release. Adding Rock Paper Scissors or Snake later doesn't require a new app listing — it's an update to the existing one, same as any app gaining features over time. The only thing to get right now is picking your package ID carefully, since changing it later effectively does create a "new app" on the store.
(There's a more advanced option — Android's Play Feature Delivery — where individual games ship as separately-downloadable modules, so users don't even redownload the whole app for a new game. Worth knowing exists, but overkill until you have many games and a real install-size problem.)
